# Application Routing

The project uses Next.js App Router with route groups for organization.

## Route Groups

- `app/(admin)/`: Admin route group
  - `app/(admin)/admin/`: Admin dashboard and functionality
  - `app/(admin)/admin/login/`: Admin login
  - `app/(admin)/admin/roles/`: Role management
  - `app/(admin)/admin/permissions/`: Permission management

- `app/(public)/`: Public route group for end users

- `app/api/`: API endpoints
  - `app/api/supabase/`: Supabase-related API endpoints

## Special Routes

- `app/forbidden/`: Access denied page
- `app/layout.tsx`: Root layout with global providers

## Middleware

- [middleware.ts](mdc:middleware.ts): Handles authentication and route protection
  - Protects admin routes
  - Redirects unauthenticated users to login
  - Checks user permissions

